[Patient] Can you recommend foods to help me manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean protein, and low-fat dairy to support heart health.
[Patient] Are there specific foods I should avoid?
[Educator] Limit sodium, processed, and high-fat foods to help manage heart failure effectively.
[Patient] I enjoy traditional meals. Can I still eat those?
[Educator] Yes, you can. We can work on modifying recipes to make them heart-healthy.
[Patient] How can I control portion sizes?
[Educator] Use smaller plates, measure portions, and listen to your body's hunger cues to control portions.
[Patient] What about snacks?
[Educator] Opt for fruits, veggies, nuts, or low-fat yogurt for heart-healthy snacking options.
[Patient] Can I still eat out at restaurants?
[Educator] Choose restaurants with heart-healthy options and ask for modifications to suit your needs.
[Patient] How can I make these changes sustainable?
[Educator] Start small, set realistic goals, and gradually incorporate healthier choices into your routine.
[Patient] Will this diet really make a difference in managing my heart failure?
[Educator] Yes, making these changes can have a significant impact on your overall health and well-being.
